definitions.definition: To release , especially in large quantities and chaotic manner.
To discard ; to get rid of something one no longer wants.
To sell below cost or very cheaply; to engage in dumping .
To copy ( data ) from a system to another place or system, usually in order to archive it.
To output the contents of storage or a data structure , often in order to diagnose a bug .
To end a romantic relationship with.
examples: Sarah dumped Nelson after finding out he was cheating on her.

definitions.definition: To put or throw down with more or less of violence; hence, to unload from a cart by tilting it
examples: We dumped the coal onto the fireplace.

definitions.definition: Of a surf wave, to crash a swimmer, surfer, etc., heavily downwards.
